After 37 years, Greyhound is shutting down its doors (Twitter @GrehoundRSA) JOHANNESBURG - Luxury coach service, Greyhound will be back on the roads again next Wednesday ahead of the busy Easter period. Greyhound and Citiliner bus lines which had been operating for 37 years ceased operating in February 2021. READ:Â Greyhound, Citiliner closing shop after 37 years The company had seen significant losses for several years, worsened by reduced travel due to COVID-19 restrictions. Its buses were then put up for auction by former owner KAP Industrial. Four thousand people lost their jobs.